 percent of which came from works priced above $1 million. <br/><br/>Since =
then, Boetti=E2=80=99s auction totals have dropped, but only because of the=
 lack of high-value sales. More Boetti lots were sold in 2023 than in 2022.=
 So far this year, as many Boetti works were sold as in all of 2022. <br/><=
br/>For an artist who made works out of humble materials and commissioned a=
rtisans to fabricate his conceptual works, it should be fitting that his ma=
rket fills out throughout lower price points. In 2023, and so far in 2024, =
less than half of the
auction value has come for works sold for seven figures. <br/><br/>Sotheby=
=E2=80=99s sold an embroidered work for $914,400. On Thursday, Christie=E2=
=80=99s will sell the remainder of a large collection of works consigned by=
